#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_Swift_SEPARATE_MODULE_EMISSION.rst:2
msgid "CMAKE_Swift_SEPARATE_MODULE_EMISSION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_Swift_SEPARATE_MODULE_EMISSION.rst:6
msgid ""
"Specify whether Swift targets emit ``.swiftmodule`` from a dedicated build "
"edge.  This variable is used to initialize the :prop_tgt:"
"`Swift_SEPARATE_MODULE_EMISSION` property on targets as they are created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_Swift_SEPARATE_MODULE_EMISSION.rst:11
msgid ""
"When set to ``ON``, importable Swift targets built by :ref:`Ninja "
"Generators` produce the ``.swiftmodule`` from a separate ``-emit-module`` "
"build edge, allowing downstream Swift targets to compile in parallel with "
"upstream object compilation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_Swift_SEPARATE_MODULE_EMISSION.rst:16
msgid ""
"If this variable is not set, separate module emission is enabled by default "
"in targets that do not set :prop_tgt:`Swift_SEPARATE_MODULE_EMISSION`. See "
"policy :policy:`CMP0215`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_Swift_SEPARATE_MODULE_EMISSION.rst:22
msgid ""
"Separate module emission takes effect only when policy :policy:`CMP0157` is "
"set to ``NEW`` prior to the first :command:`project` or :command:"
"`enable_language` command that enables the Swift language."
msgstr ""
